            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gamespot.com/articles/advance-wars-lookalike-game-warside-is-out-now/1100-6530843/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6530843">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>The Advance Wars lookalike tactics game Warside, developed by Lavabird and published by First Break Labs, is out now on PC. However, fans have pointed out that it's buggy and seemingly unfinished, reflecting its Mostly Negative reception so far.</p><p>Warside looks eerily similar, if not almost identical, to Advance Wars. The maps, buildings, battles, and troops look very much like the ones in Nintendo's tactics franchise. The biggest differentiator is that the Commanders in Warside have a more realistic pixel art as opposed to Advance Wars' anime art style.</p><p>According to the <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/2368300/Warside/#app_reviews_hash" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Steam reviews section</a>, there are several features and gameplay mechanics that are missing. One player said that Warside feels like an early access release, with multiplayer lobbies and local multiplayer functionality nowhere to be found, even though both features were advertised as available.</p><p>Another player noted that the game's economy is broken as income needed to purchase troops is unavailable. However, it seems like the developers have already quickly fixed that issue.</p><p>Warside isn't the only game that's attempting to capture the spirit of the Game Boy Advance era, as the recently released <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/this-classic-fire-emblem-inspired-rpg-launches-in-march/1100-6529734/" data-ref-id="1100-6529734">Dark Deity 2</a> is inspired by Fire Emblem games from that period.</p><p>Warside currently has a 10% launch discount and will be coming to PlayStation, Switch, and Xbox at a <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/03/warside-launches-april-14-for-pc-later-for-ps5-xbox-series-ps4-xbox-one-and-switch" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener">later date</a>.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
