          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p dir="ltr">Want to watch a cute kitty paw at a taskbar and earn hats? Then Bongo Cat should be right up your alley. In fact, the free-to-play game has clearly struck a chord with a wide swath of people, as over 125,000 people are playing it right now (at time of publication), per <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/charts/mostplayed" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Steam</a>.</p><p dir="ltr"><a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/3419430/Bongo_Cat/" rel="nofollow ">Bongo Cat</a> is a clicker game that sees a feline patting a taskbar with its paws as a player types or clicks a mouse. That increases your points and treasure chests will eventually appear, too, containing different types of hats. There are <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/news/app/3419430/view/519709240792712815?l=english" rel="nofollow ">20 exclusive items tied to an event this month</a> that runs through April 22. That same announcement on March 31 noted that Bongo Cat has seen over 500,000 different players. It was also one of <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/steam-next-fest-winter-2025s-most-popular-demos-include-game-of-thrones-and-dune/2900-6299/#1" data-ref-id="2900-6299">the most popular demos from Steam Next Fest in February</a>.</p><p dir="ltr"><a href="https://steamdb.info/app/3419430/charts/#max" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">The SteamDB chart</a> shows that Bongo Cat was averaging about 40,000 concurrent players for the second half of March before exploding at the beginning of this month. The clicker game hit a peak of 134,411 players yesterday but has been pretty close to topping that number today. It's <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/this-massive-and-inexplicably-popular-banana-game-adds-new-skins/1100-6524446/">not quite as popular as Banana</a> from last year, but Bongo Cat seems to scratch a similar itch. The game is seeing <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/3419430/Bongo_Cat/#app_reviews_hash" rel="nofollow ">"overwhelmingly positive" reviews</a> so far on Steam.</p><p>Last month, <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/repo-has-come-out-of-nowhere-on-steam-topping-145000-concurrent-players/1100-6530038/">REPO came out of nowhere on Steam</a> with more than 145,000 concurrent players. The cooperative horror game continues to see a steady stream of players and has even made some waves <a href="https://www.twitch.tv/directory/category/r-e-p-o">on Twitch</a>. For more, check out GameSpot's list of <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/top-20-most-popular-steam-games-of-all-time/2900-6301/#1">the top 20 most popular Steam games of all time</a>.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
